description: AmoFunction: Table storing AMO function configuration parameters for each cell in a given area at a specific point in time.  Columns: dateTime (timestamp of data), Area_Name (geographic area), CellId (unique cell identifier), Id2 (duplicate of CellId), Id3 (apparently redundant ID), vsDataType (data type identifier), vsDataFormatVersion (version of data format), AmoFunction.amoFunctionId (AMO function ID), AmoFunction.allowInterVendorX2Signal (flag indicating inter-vendor X2 signaling support), AmoFunction.amoAllowedInterVendor (flag indicating inter-vendor AMO support).
